There are some other view elements:
• iterates through all elements in modules.json
• instantiates a module for each entry
• each module gets its configuration object from modules.json passed to the constructor
• calls hgInit() on all newly created modules
• emits signal onAllModulesLoaded when all modules are loaded
each modules get the HG.HistoGlobe instance as parameter of the the hgInit() call --- this can be used to access all other loaded modules
• creates a HG.HiventMarker2D for each Hivent
• representative for a Hivent on the map
• provides many callbacks for hivent controlling

• for example, when a HG.HiventMarker2D gets a mouse click, it will call activate() on the handle --- this will emit the onActive callback which can be used by other modules which may use this to open pop-up windows for instance

• adds two important public methods to a class when used as mixin (and two less important ones)
addCallback(name): Adds a new callback to the calling object. This means that a method called "name" will be added to the object which can be be used by other objects to register listener functions.
notifyAll(name): Calls all registered listener functions.
